{
  "title": "A hybrid learning approach for MRI-based detection of alzheimer’s disease stages using dual CNNs and ensemble classifier - Nature",
  "url": "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-11743-y",
  "content": "This study presents a combination of two parallel Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and an ensemble learning method for classifying AD stages using Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) data. The selected features were fed into an ensemble learning with soft voting, combining Support Vector Machine (SVM), Random Forest (RF), and K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) classifiers to achieve final classification accuracy across Alzheimer’s stages, with hyperparameters optimized via the Grid Search Cross-Validation (GridSearchCV) method. In this work, a dual-CNN structure combining the outputs of Network 1 and Network 2 was utilized to extract salient features from MRI images, along with an ensemble learning method to perform AD classification."
